cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ReCompress, please cite it as below."
title: "ReCompress: Query-Aware Rewriting and Tiered Memory for Efficient LLM Context Compression"
abstract: >-
  ReCompress is a two-component context-compression system. A query-aware rewriting
  compressor, distilled into a 1.5B student (Qwen2.5-1.5B + LoRA), beats the deletion-based
  bear-2 by +0.252 F1 on HotpotQA while emitting ~8.5x fewer tokens, and a tiered
  multi-turn memory (RbD-Compress / Re:Zero) keeps the context sent to the solver flat across
  a conversation. Built in 24h for The Token Company Compression Challenge at the UC Berkeley
  AI Hackathon 2026.
type: software
